{{for|other uses of "Zimmermann"|Zimmermann (disambiguation)}} '''Eberhardt August Wilhelm von Zimmermann''' (August 17, 1743, [[Uelzen]] &ndash; July 4, 1815, [[Braunschweig]]) was a German [[geographer]] and [[zoologist]].
He studied [[natural philosophy]] and [[mathematics]] in [[Leiden]], [[Halle an der Saale|Halle]], [[Berlin]], and [[Göttingen]], and in 1766 was appointed professor of mathematics and [[natural sciences]] at the [[TU Braunschweig|Collegium Carolinum in Braunschweig]]. One of his pupils was mathematician [[Carl Friedrich Gauss]].<ref name=PR>[http://libweb5.princeton.edu/visual_materials/maps/websites/thematic-maps/quantitative/natural-history/natural-history.html Natural History - Princeton University Library]</ref> From 1789 onward, he served as aulic councillor in Braunschweig.<ref name=DB>[http://www.deutsche-biographie.de/sfz86676.html Zimmermann, Eberhard August Wilhelm von] at Deutsche Biographie</ref><ref name=SA>[https://books.google.com/books?id=1NVRfl4gCw0C&pg=PA701&lpg=PA701 Thibaut - Zycha, Volume 10] by K. G. Saur Verlag GmbH & Company, Walter De Gruyter Incorporated</ref>
During his career, he travelled widely throughout Europe &mdash; [[Livonia]], Russia, Sweden, Denmark. England, France, Germany, Switzerland, and Italy. On his journeys, he conducted research of economic conditions and natural resources.<ref name=PR/> He wrote ''Specimen Zoologiae Geographicae Quadrupedum'' (1777), one of the first works on the geographical distribution of [[mammal]]s ([[zoogeography]]).
He was the author of works on a variety of subjects, such as mathematics, natural sciences, regional studies, and the history of discovery. From 1802 to 1813, he published the ''Taschenbuch der Reisen'' (''Handbook of Travel'').<ref name=SA/>
== Published works == * ''Geographische geschichte des menschen und der allgemein verbreiteten vierfüssigen thiere'', 3 volumes (1779–1783) &ndash; Geographical history of humans and the general distribution of quadrupeds. * ''Über die Elastizität des Wassers'', 1779 &ndash; On the elasticity of water. * {{Cite book |title=Voyage a la nitrière naturelle qui se trouve à Molfetta dans la terre de Bari en Pouille |year=1790 |publisher=Jacque Storti |location=[[Venice]] |volume= |url=https://books.google.co.th/books?id=w35066b2qG8C&pg=PA1#v=onepage&q&f=false |ref=zimmermann-nitriere}} * ''Frankreich und die Freistaaten von Nordamerika'', (part I, 1795; part II, 1800) &ndash; France and the free states of [[North America]]. * ''Die erde und ihre bewohner. Ein lesebuch für geographie, völkerkunde produktenlehre und den handel'', 5 volumes (1810–1814) &ndash; The earth and its inhabitants. A reading book of geography, [[ethnology]], etc.<ref>[http://catalog.hathitrust.org/Search/Home?lookfor=%22Zimmermann,%20Eberhard%20August%20Wilhelm%20von,%201743-1815.%22&type=author&inst= Catalog HathiTrust] published works</ref><ref name=DB/><ref name=SA/>
