{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2016}}


An '''environmental organization''' is an [[organization]] coming out of the [[Conservation movement|conservation]] or [[environmental movement]]s
that seeks to protect, analyse or monitor the environment against misuse or [[environmental degradation|degradation]] [[Human impact on the environment|from human forces]].

In this sense the environment may refer to the [[environment (biophysical)|biophysical environment]], the [[natural environment]] or the [[built environment]]. The organization may be a [[Charitable organization|charity]], a [[trust law|trust]], a [[non-governmental organization]] or a government organization. Environmental organizations can be global, [[Country|national]], [[Subregion|regional]] or local.

== History ==
Founded on 28 May 1892 in [[San Francisco]], [[California]], [[Sierra Club]] was one of the first large-scale environmental preservation organizations in the world.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sierraclub.org/about|title=About the Sierra Club|work=[[Sierra Club]]}}</ref>

== Politics ==
Most organizations exert more influence through their involvement in [[policy making]]. [[Green politics]] is a political ideology which emphasizes the importance of achieving environmental goals. The [[Green party|Green parties]] have formed to implement [[environmental policies]] at a government level.

== Issues in focus ==
[[File:Audubon Center at Bent of the River III.JPG|thumb|Audubon Center at Bent of the River. The Audubon Society is an environmental organization dedicated to the protection of birds.]]
Some [[environmental issue]]s that environmental organizations focus on include [[pollution]], [[waste]], [[resource depletion]], [[human overpopulation]] and [[climate change]].
{{further information|List of environmental issues}}

== List of environmental organizations ==
[[File:Greenpeace logo.svg|thumb|[[Greenpeace]] logo. The organization is one of the most visible interest groups worldwide]]
{{Main article|List of environmental organizations}}
{{further information|List of anti-nuclear groups||Sustainability organizations|:Category:Environmental organizations}}

Notable global environmental organizations are the [[United Nations Environment Programme]] (UNEP), [[World Wide Fund for Nature]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.panda.org/about_wwf/where_we_work/project/|title=WWF conservation projects around the world|publisher=[[World Wide Fund for Nature]]}}</ref>  the [[Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change]] (IPCC), [[Greenpeace]] and [[Friends of the Earth]].

== Counter-movements ==
Many [[interest group]]s and associations have been formed, often industry supported, to counter the progressive - [[Criticism of capitalism|capitalism-]] and [[Criticism of libertarianism|economy-skeptic]] attitude and influence of environmental organizations. However, these interest groups are rarely pure in [[ideological]] nature.
{{further information|Category:Organizations of environmentalism skeptics and critics|environmental skepticism|anti-environmentalism}}

