[[File:2008 LekkiMarket Lagos Nigeria 2349218847.jpg|thumb|right|Lekki Market, Lagos, 2008]] [[File:2005 market Lagos Nigeria 12129001.jpg|thumb|right|Market, Lagos, 2003]] Markets in [[Lagos]], [[Nigeria]], offer a broad and diverse range of new, second-hand goods, products and merchandise for consumers.
Notable markets in Lagos include: {{Expand list|date=September 2014}} * [[Alaba international market]] * [[Balogun Market|Balogun Market, Lagos Island]]<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.aboutlagos.com/?p=776|title=Balogun Market|website=About Lagos|accessdate=September 7, 2014}}</ref> * Bar Beach Market<ref name=planet1999 /> * [[Computer Village]]<ref>{{cite news|author=Josfyn Uba|author2=Christine Onwuachuba |date=August 6, 2013|url=http://sunnewsonline.com/new/?p=35675|title=The Biggest Markets in Lagos|work=The Sun|accessdate=September 7, 2014}}</ref> * [[Ebute Ero market|Èbúté Èrò Market]], Lagos Island<ref name=planet1999 /> * Ekpe Fish Market<ref name=planet1999 /> * [[Ikotun Market]] * [[Idumota Market]] * Isale Eko Market, Lagos Island<ref name=planet1999>{{Citation |publisher = [[Lonely Planet]] |title= West Africa |edition=4th |year=1999 |ol= 8314753M |chapter=Nigeria: Lagos |chapterurl=https://archive.org/stream/lonelyplanetwest00davi#page/710/mode/1up |pages= 710+ }}</ref> * Jankarra Market, Lagos Island<ref name=planet1999 /> * [[Ladipo Market]] * Lekki Market<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deltaskymag.delta.com/Destinations/Lagos/Shopping/Lekki-Market.aspx|website=Delta Sky|title=Lagos:Lekki Market|accessdate=September 19, 2014}}</ref> * Morocco I and II markets<ref name=planet1999 /> * Mushin market<ref>{{cite web|url=http://travelbagslaptopp.blogspot.com/2012/04/some-favorite-markets-in-lagos-nigeria.html?m=1|title=Some favorite markets in Lagos, Nigeria|date=April 12, 2012|accessdate=September 7, 2014|website=Travelbagslaptop}}</ref> * [[Oyingbo Market]] * [[Mile 12 Market]] * [[Oshodi Market]]<ref>{{cite book|editor=Kerstin Pinther|title=Afropolis: City Media Art |year=2012|publisher=Jacana Media |isbn=978-1-4314-0325-7 |chapterurl= https://books.google.com/books?id=9lcn62brtGQC&pg=PA138 |chapter=Lagos-Oshodi |author=Peter Probst |display-editors=etal}}</ref> * Rauf Aregbesola Market<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.vanguardngr.com/2013/10/lagos-markets-shut-akiolu-instals-tinubu-ojo-iyaloja-general/|title=Lagos Markets shut down as Akiolu installs Tinubu Ojo as Iyaloja|work=Vanguard|accessdate=September 7, 2014}}</ref> * [[Tejuosho Market|Téjúoshó Market]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.firstbanknigeria.com/media/media-space/press-releases/firstbank-financed-ultra-modern-tejuosho-market-re-opens-in-lagos/|title=First bank financed ultramodern Tejuosho market reopens in Lagos|accessdate=September 7, 2014}}</ref>
