{{Crisis in Bolivarian Venezuela}}
'''[[Venezuelan protests (2014–present)|The 2015 Venezuelan protests]]''' began in the first days of January primarily due to [[shortages in Venezuela]],<ref name=SVCOprotest2>{{cite news|title=En 2014 se registraron 9.286 protestas, cifra inédita en Venezuela|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2015/01/19/en-2014-se-registraron-9-286-protestas-cifra-inedita-en-venezuela/|accessdate=25 January 2015|agency=La Patilla|date=19 January 2015}}</ref> with the first massive demonstration occurring on 23 January.<ref name=JAN23>{{cite news|last1=Leon|first1=Leonardo|title=Miles de merideños marcharon contra la crisis económica y la represión contra los estudiantes|url=http://www.el-nacional.com/regiones/Miles-marcharon-economica-represion-estudiantes_0_561543941.html|accessdate=24 January 2015|agency=El Nacional|date=23 January 2015}}</ref> [[Timeline of the 2014 Venezuelan protests|The series of protests originally began in February 2014]] when hundreds of thousands of Venezuelans protested due to high levels of criminal violence, inflation, and chronic scarcity of basic goods because of policies created the [[Venezuelan government]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Lopez|first=Linette|title=Why The United States Has Done Nothing About Venezuela|url=http://www.businessinsider.com/why-the-us-wont-touch-venezuela-2014-4|accessdate=12 April 2014|newspaper=Business Insider|date=11 April 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Protesters in Venezuela Press Government|url=https://online.wsj.com/news/articles/SB10001424052702304834704579401612202743396|accessdate=12 April 2014|newspaper=The Wall Street Journal|date=23 February 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Venezuelans protest en masse in rival rallies|url=http://www.theborneopost.com/2014/02/24/venezuelans-protest-en-masse-in-rival-rallies/|accessdate=12 April 2014|newspaper=Borneo Post|date=24 February 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| title= Venezuela's Maduro says 2013 annual inflation was 56.2 pct|url= https://www.reuters.com/article/2013/12/30/venezuela-inflation-annual-idUSL2N0K90V020131230 |accessdate= 19 January 2014|newspaper= Reuters|date= 30 December 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | title = Venezuela Inflation Hits 16-Year High as Shortages Rise|url= https://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-11-07/venezuela-inflation-hits-16-year-high-as-shortages-rise.html |accessdate=16 February 2014|newspaper= Bloomberg|date= 7 November 2013}}</ref> As of January 2015, over 50 people had been arrested for protesting.<ref name=REUT2015jan16>{{cite news|last1=Ulmer|first1=Alexander|title=Venezuela's 'protest city' on edge as economic crisis worsens|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2015/01/16/us-venezuela-protests-idUSKBN0KP1L320150116|accessdate=16 January 2015|agency=Reuters|date=16 January 2015}}</ref> The protests are listed below according to the month they had happened.
==January== [[File:March of Empty Pots 24 January 2015.jpg|250px|thumbnail|right|The "March of Empty Pots" in Caracas on 24 January 2015, where several thousand marched against shortages and denounced the Venezuelan government.]] [[File:Altamira protest 5 January 2015.jpg|250px|thumb|right|A vigil being held on 5 January 2015 for those killed and imprisoned during the 2014 Venezuelan protests.]] [[File:Caracas shortage protest 23 January 2015.jpg|250px|thumb|right|Protesters showing signs and yelling invitations to protest to the people in lines waiting to buy basic goods.]] * '''1 January'''&nbsp;– Students who chained themselves together in [[Altamira Square|Plaza Altamira]] on 18 December 2014 remained chained and demanded the release of arrested protesters and stated that their actions "achieved the objective of generating reflection Venezuelans about the situation of political prisoners in the country."<ref>{{cite news|title=Estudiantes levantan la protesta en la Plaza Altamira (Comunicado)|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2015/01/01/estudiantes-levantan-la-protesta-en-la-plaza-altamira-comunicado/|accessdate=13 January 2015|agency=[[La Patilla]]|date=1 January 2015}}</ref> Three people remained chained together in [[Maracay]] after three consecutive days stating that they wish to stay at the site for at least six days to "call to the conscience".<ref>{{cite news|title=Jóvenes cumplen tres días de protesta encadenados Prevén extender manifestación 6 días más|url=http://www.elperiodiquito.com/article/183403/Jovenes-cumplen-tres-dias-de-protesta-encadenados|accessdate=13 January 2015|agency=El Periodiquito|date=1 January 2015}}</ref> * '''3 January'''&nbsp;– Several people began protesting in [[Los Teques]] due to the long lines to purchase goods.<ref>{{cite news|title=Protesta en Los Teques por escasez de leche en polvo (Fotos)|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2015/01/03/trancan-canal-de-la-panamericana-por-protesta/|accessdate=13 January 2015|agency=La Patilla|date=3 January 2015}}</ref> * '''5 January'''&nbsp;–Peaceful protests occurred on Francisco Miranda Avenue in Chacao denouncing the poor situation of Venezuela while demanding the release of protesters arrest by the National Guard.<ref>{{cite news|title=Chacao protesta este #6E (Fotos)|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2015/01/06/chacao-protesta-este-6e-fotos/|accessdate=13 January 2015|agency=La Patilla|date=6 January 2015}}</ref> * '''6 January'''&nbsp;– Students held a peaceful protest on Las Delicias Avenue in Maracay to send a message to Venezuela and the international community showing solidarity with arrested protesters while also criticizing the security policies of the Bolivarian government.<ref>{{cite news|title=Con las manos encadenadasDirigentes estudiantiles protestaron pacíficamente en la Av. Las Delicias|url=http://www.elsiglo.com.ve/article/96622/Dirigentes-estudiantiles-protestaron-pacificamente-en-la-Av--Las-Delicias|accessdate=13 January 2015|agency=[[El Siglo (Venezuela)|El Siglo]]|date=6 January 2015}}</ref> Protesters demonstrated for a second day on Francisco Miranda Avenue in Chacao addressing the social, economic and political crisis in Venezuela while also asking for the release of those arrested.<ref>{{cite news|title=En Chacao realizaron pancartazo contra la crisis en Venezuela (Video)|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2015/01/07/en-chacao-realizaron-pancartazo-contra-la-crisis-en-venezuela-video/|accessdate=13 January 2015|agency=La Patilla|date=7 January 2015}}</ref> * '''7 January'''&nbsp;– Students from the Catholic University of Táchira peacefully protested on the main street of [[San Cristóbal, Táchira|San Cristobal]] which resulted in 12 arrested, including 4 minors.<ref>{{cite news|title=Así arrestó la PNB a los estudiantes en Táchira #7E (Video)|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2015/01/07/asi-arresto-la-pnb-a-los-estudiantes-en-tachira-7e-video/|accessdate=14 January 2015|agency=La Patilla|date=7 January 2015}}</ref> * '''8 January'''&nbsp;– For the fourth consecutive day, protests occurred in Chacao with barricades reappearing, which resulted in response from authorities with tear gas.<ref>{{cite news|title=Vuelven las barricadas y las lacrimógenas a Chacao; PNB armó un piquete #8E (Fotos)|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2015/01/08/vuelven-las-barricadas-y-las-lacrimogenas-a-chacao-pnb-armo-un-piquete-8e-fotos/|accessdate=14 January 2015|agency=La Patilla|date=8 January 2015}}</ref> The Pan American Highway was blocked by students in Los Toques causing heavy back ups.<ref>{{cite news|title=Colapsada la Panamericana por protesta (FOTO)|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2015/01/08/colapsada-la-panamericana-por-protesta-foto/|accessdate=14 January 2015|agency=La Patilla|date=8 January 2015}}</ref> * '''9 January'''&nbsp;– After clashes with protesters, the National Guard and National Police destroyed memorabilia of those injured or killed during the protests.<ref>{{cite news|title=Lamentable provocación: GNB pisotea homenaje a caídos en protesta ubicado en Altamira|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2015/01/09/lamentable-provocacion-gnb-pisotea-homenaje-a-caidos-en-protesta-ubicado-en-altamira/|accessdate=14 January 2015|agency=La Patilla|date=9 January 2015}}</ref> Five individuals were arrested in Chacao for possessing gas masks.<ref>{{cite news|title=Reportan cinco detenidos en Chacao #9E (Fotos)|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2015/01/09/reportan-cinco-detenidos-en-chacao-9e-fotos/|accessdate=14 January 2015|agency=La Patilla|date=9 January 2015}}</ref> Residents of La Candelaria protested due to long lines that mostly last more than 8 hours and shortages in stores.<ref>{{cite news|title=La Candelaria salió a protestar, vecinos están hartos de las colas (Fotos)|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2015/01/09/la-candelaria-salio-a-protestar-vecinos-estan-hartos-de-las-colas-fotos/|accessdate=14 January 2015|agency=La Patilla|date=9 January 2015}}</ref> * '''10 January'''&nbsp;– In Santa Fe, protesters blocked traffic on Prados del Este Highway and attempted to construct a barricade, but were dispersed in about 30 minutes.<ref>{{cite news|title=Guardia Nacional dispersó manifestantes en Santa Fe|url=http://www.eluniversal.com/nacional-y-politica/150110/guardia-nacional-disperso-manifestantes-en-santa-fe|accessdate=15 January 2015|agency=El Universal|date=10 January 2015}}</ref> 5 individuals were arrested in San Bernardino after protesting near a government Bicentennial market.<ref>{{cite news|title=Detenidos en San Bernardino fueron trasladados a Cotiza|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2015/01/10/detenidos-en-san-bernardino-fueron-trasladados-a-cotiza/|accessdate=14 January 2015|agency=La Patilla|date=10 January 2015}}</ref> * '''12 January'''&nbsp;– Opposition leader [[Henrique Capriles Radonski]] said it was time for Venezuelans to mobilize following growing shortages and large lines for food in January, but noted that it was "not the time of guarimba".<ref name=EU14jan>{{cite news|url=http://www.eluniversal.com.mx/el-mundo/2015/capriles-movilizacion-oposicion-evenezuela-1068715.html|accessdate=15 January 2015|agency=[[El Universal (Mexico)]]|date=14 January 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Es momento de la movilización, no de las guarimbas, afirmó Capriles|url=http://elimpulso.com/articulo/es-momento-de-la-movilizacion-no-de-las-guarimbas-afirmo-capriles|accessdate=15 January 2015|agency=[[El Impulso]]|date=12 January 2015}}</ref> In [[Naguanagua]], protests and authorities clashed with tear gas being fired by the National Guard.<ref>{{cite news|title=PNB y GNB irrumpen edificios en Naguanagua buscando manifestantes (FOTOS)|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2015/01/12/pnb-y-gnb-irrumpen-edificios-en-naguanagua-buscando-manifestantes-fotos/|accessdate=14 January 2015|agency=La Patilla|date=12 January 2015}}</ref> * '''13 January'''&nbsp;– The Catholic University of Táchira suspended classes due to strong protests in the area that left more than 20 students injured.<ref>{{cite news|title=Universidad Católica del Táchira suspende clases luego de fuerte protesta|url=http://www.eluniversal.com/nacional-y-politica/150113/universidad-catolica-del-tachira-suspende-clases-luego-de-fuerte-prote|accessdate=15 January 2015|agency=El Universal|date=13 January 2015}}</ref> The [[Democratic Unity Roundtable]] proposed a possible "mobilization" following a call made by Henrique Capriles due to the "massive violation of human rights" in Venezuela.<ref>{{cite news|title=MUD prepara agenda de movilización|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2015/01/13/mud-prepara-agenda-de-movilizacion/|accessdate=14 January 2015|agency=La Patilla|date=13 January 2015}}</ref> * '''14 January'''&nbsp;– Students in Mérida begin to protest against insecurity as well as food and medicine shortages.<ref name=LP15jan2015>{{cite news|title=Merideños salen a la calle y exigen renuncia de Maduro #15E (Fotos)|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2015/01/15/meridenos-salen-a-la-calle-y-exigen-renuncia-de-maduro-15e-fotos/|accessdate=16 January 2015|agency=La Patilla|date=16 January 2015}}</ref> Students in [[San Cristobal, Bolívar]] protested because of nationwide shortages by blocking streets and burning tires.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Ulmer|first1=Alexandra|title=Venezuela's 'protest city' on edge as economic crisis worsens|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2015/01/16/us-venezuela-protests-idUSKBN0KP1L320150116|accessdate=18 January 2015|agency=Reuters|date=16 January 2015}}</ref> * '''15 January'''&nbsp;– At the University of Los Andes (ULA) in Tachira, Venezuelan authorities and possibly members of [[Colectivo (Venezuela)|colectivos]] raided the university firing teargas and buckshot at student protesters.<ref>{{cite news|title=GNB y PNB violan autonomía universitaria en Táchira y disparan metras a estudiantes (FOTOS)|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2015/01/15/gnb-y-pnb-violan-autonomia-universitaria-en-tachira-y-disparan-metras-a-estudiantes-fotos/|accessdate=16 January 2015|agency=La Patilla|date=15 January 2015}}</ref><ref name=LNjan2015>{{cite news|title=Heridos estudiantes de la ULA con perdigones de plomo y metras|url=http://www.lanacion.com.ve/sucesos/heridos-estudiantes-de-la-ula-con-perdigones-de-plomo-y-metras/|accessdate=16 January 2015|agency=La Nación|date=16 January 2015}}</ref> Venezuelan authorities broke down doors to enter facilities and fired at students inside of the buildings.<ref name=LNjan2015/> At least 25 students were injured from both lead and plastic pellets fired from Venezuelan authorities at the ULA protest, with the injured students being treated by medical students on campus in order to avoid arrests.<ref name=LNjan2015/> In Mérida, students protested once again with horns of passing cars heard showing support.<ref name=LP15jan2015/> * '''18 January'''&nbsp;– During the 2015 Vuelta al Táchira circuit, peaceful protesters were confronted by National Guardsmen.<ref>{{cite news|title=GNB agrede a diputados y concejales del Táchira que realizaban protesta pacífica (Video)|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2015/01/18/gnb-agrede-a-diputados-y-concejales-del-tachira-que-realizaban-protesta-pacifica-video/|accessdate=20 January 2015|agency=La Patilla|date=18 January 2015}}</ref> * '''19 January'''&nbsp;– Active and retired teachers protested in Táchira demanding the resignation of regional board and national administrator of the Venezuelan government's Institute for Social Security and Welfare Staff of the Ministry of Education (IPASME) due to what they call proselytizing and propaganda produced by the institution.<ref>{{cite news|title=Con pancartazo docentes en Táchira exigieron aumento de sueldos #19E (Fotos)|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2015/01/19/con-pancartazo-docentes-en-tachira-exigieron-aumento-de-sueldos-19e-fotos/|accessdate=20 January 2015|agency=La Patilla|date=19 January 2015}}</ref> * '''22 January'''&nbsp;– In [[Piar Municipality, Bolívar|Piar]], members of the Chamber of Commerce and Industry protested demanding security from the state government, law enforcement agencies and regional authorities.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Martínez|first1=María|title=Piarenses marcharon para reclamar seguridad|url=http://www.nuevaprensa.com.ve/Piarenses%20marcharon%20para%20reclamar%20seguridad|accessdate=24 January 2015|agency=Nueva Prensa|date=22 January 2015}}</ref> * '''23 January'''&nbsp;– Venezuelans across the country gathered with the opposition denouncing inabilities of the Venezuelan government demanding freedom and democracy while commemorating the end of [[Marcos Pérez Jiménez]]'s dictatorship in Venezuela.<ref>{{cite news|title=Oposición venezolana manifestó en todo el país este 23-E (Fotos)|url=http://diariodecaracas.com/que-sucede/oposicion-venezolana-manifesto-en-todo-el-pais-este-23-e-fotos|accessdate=24 January 2015|agency=El Diario de Caracas|date=23 January 2015}}</ref> Thousands peacefully demonstrated through a march in [[Mérida, Mérida|Mérida]], marching over 4&nbsp;km denouncing Venezuela's economic situation from the University of Los Andes to the Ombudsman's office delivering a document.<ref name=JAN23/> An hour after the march ended, a separate protest gathered that was confronted by motorcyclists that beat one student and left them shot in the ankle.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Leon|first1=Leonardo|title=Reportan estudiantes y policías heridos en protestas en Mérida|url=http://www.el-nacional.com/regiones/Reportan-estudiantes-policias-protestas-Merida_0_561544053.html|accessdate=24 January 2015|agency=El Nacional|date=23 January 2015}}</ref> Clashes also occurred in Mérida between protesters and Venezuelan authorities that resulted in a damaged National Guard vehicle and the use of force on the protesters.<ref>{{cite news|title=Manifestantes atacan ballena (Fotos)|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2015/01/23/lluvia-de-perdigones-y-lacrimogenas-en-merida-manifestantes-atacan-ballena-fotos/|accessdate=24 January 2015|agency=La Patilla|date=23 January 2015}}</ref> The clashes occurred in Mérida after Venezuelan authorities encountered a protest by citizens that was held due to a lack of gas in their homes for nearly 2 weeks.<ref>{{cite news|title=PoliMérida atacó a manifestantes que protestaron por falta de gas (Video)|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2015/01/24/polimerida-ataco-a-manifestantes-que-protestaron-por-falta-de-gas-video/|accessdate=28 January 2015|agency=La Patilla|date=24 January 2015}}</ref> The MUD opposition group called for a nationwide protest called the "March of Empty Pots" for the next day, 24 January.<ref>{{cite news|title=Este sábado será la "marchas de las ollas vacías" (y morgues llenas) en protesta por la situación nacional|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2015/01/23/unidad-convoca-a-marchas-de-las-ollas-vacias-para-este-sabado/|accessdate=24 January 2015|agency=La Patilla|date=23 January 2015}}</ref> * '''24 January'''&nbsp;– Several thousand Venezuelans protested in the "March of Empty Pots" in Caracas against the shortages of products and demanded changes in the Venezuelan government.<ref name=BLOOMjan2015>{{cite news|last1=Rosati|first1=Andrew|last2=Crooks|first2=Nathan|title=Venezuela Opposition March Ends After Police Scuffles|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/2015-01-24/venezuela-capital-sees-rival-street-marches-as-economy-struggles.html|accessdate=28 January 2015|agency=Bloomberg|date=24 January 2015}}</ref><ref name=ABCjan2015>{{cite news|title=Thousands March Against Socialist President in Venezuela|url=http://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/thousands-march-socialist-president-venezuela-28455387|accessdate=28 January 2015|agency=ABC News|date=24 January 2015}}</ref> In Zulia, a march was held from the University of Zulia to the Republic Plaza, where speeches by opposition leaders were held.<ref>{{cite news|title=La Unidad zuliana tomó las calles contra la crisis (FOTOS)|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2015/01/24/la-unidad-zuliana-tomo-las-calles-contra-la-crisis-fotos/|accessdate=28 January 2015|agency=La Patilla|date=24 January 2015}}</ref> The protests were smaller than the other organized demonstrations in 2014 since Venezuelans feared a government crackdown or were preoccupied with the product shortages in the country.<ref name=ABCjan2015/> * '''25 January'''&nbsp;– In Chacao, residents protested in the evening under the watch of Venezuelan authorities.<ref>{{cite news|title=Video: El pancartazo de este 25e bajo la mirada de la GNB y en total calma|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2015/01/25/video-el-pancartazo-de-este-25e-bajo-la-mirada-de-la-gnb-y-en-total-calma/|accessdate=6 February 2015|agency=La Patilla|date=25 January 2015}}</ref> * '''26 January'''&nbsp;– In Los Teques, students of the College of Los Teques "Cecilio Acosta" (CULTCA) protested which led to the response from the National Guard entering the campus firing tear gas and rubber bullets.<ref>{{cite news|title=GNB le cayó a perdigones y lacrimógenas a estudiantes en el Cultca Los Teques #26E (Fotos)|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2015/01/26/gnb-le-cayo-a-perdigones-y-lacrimogenas-a-estudiantes-en-el-cultca-los-teques-26e-fotos/|accessdate=6 February 2015|agency=La Patilla|date=26 January 2015}}</ref> * '''27 January'''&nbsp;– The Government of Venezuela authorizes the use of lethal force as a "last resort" for protests despite a constitutional ban on the use of toxic weapons or use of firearms.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Lopez|first1=Edgar|title=Autorizan uso de armas mortales contra protestas|url=http://www.el-nacional.com/politica/Autorizan-uso-armas-mortales-protestas_0_564543734.html|accessdate=12 February 2015|agency=El Nacional|date=29 January 2015|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150216080935/http://www.el-nacional.com/politica/Autorizan-uso-armas-mortales-protestas_0_564543734.html|archivedate=16 February 2015|df=}}</ref> In Mérida, 18 students, including multiple minors, were arrested in the evening for allegedly being part of a protest.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Sanchez|first1=Nora|title=Detenidos 19 estudiantes por protestar en Mérida|url=http://www.eluniversal.com/nacional-y-politica/150128/detenidos-19-estudiantes-por-protestar-en-merida|accessdate=6 February 2015|agency=El Universal|date=28 January 2015}}</ref> * '''28 January'''&nbsp;– At the University Rafael Belloso Chacin (Urbe) in Maracaibo, students who were protesting for the release of other students that had been previously arrested were allegedly confronted by both the National Police and colectivos working together.<ref>{{cite news|title=Aparecen los colectivos durante represión de la PNB a estudiantes de Urbe (Fotos)|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2015/01/28/aparecen-los-colectivos-durante-represion-de-la-pnb-a-estudiantes-de-urbe-fotos/|accessdate=6 February 2015|agency=La Patilla|date=28 January 2015}}</ref> * '''29 January'''&nbsp;– After being detained for two days, the 18 students who were arrested in Mérida were released while citizens protested outside of the police station.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Sanchez|first1=Nora|title=Libertad plena para 18 detenidos en manifestaciones en Mérida|url=http://www.eluniversal.com/nacional-y-politica/150129/libertad-plena-para-18-detenidos-en-manifestaciones-en-merida|accessdate=6 February 2015|agency=El Universal|date=29 January 2015}}</ref>
==February== [[File:Liberty 12 February 2015 Venezuelan protest.jpg|250px|thumb|right|Protester during the rally called by the students on February 12th in Caracas.]] [[File:2015 Venezuela protest 20 February.jpg|250px|thumb|right|María Corina Machado and Lilian Tintori supporting Mrs. Mitzy Capriles de Ledezma, wife of the Metropolitan Mayor of Caracas at a gathering on 20 February.]] * '''3 February'''&nbsp;– Students of the University of Los Andes called for a march to the Public Ministry in Mérida on 12 February, commemorating the deaths of those killed that day one year beforehand and to demand the release of arrested students.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Sanchez|first1=Nora|title=Estudiantes de la ULA convocan a marcha para el 12F|url=http://www.eluniversal.com/nacional-y-politica/150203/estudiantes-de-la-ula-convocan-a-marcha-para-el-12f|accessdate=6 February 2015|agency=El Universal|date=3 February 2014}}</ref> * '''4 February'''&nbsp;– In Mérida, members of the "Liberation Movement" of the University of Los Andes along with residents protested demanding the resignation of President Maduro.<ref>{{cite news|title=#MaduroRenuncia: La consigna de la protesta merideña de este miércoles (FOTOS)|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2015/02/04/madurorenuncia-la-consigna-de-la-protesta-meridena-de-este-miercoles-fotos/|accessdate=6 February 2015|agency=La Patilla|date=4 February 2015}}</ref> * '''7 February'''&nbsp;– In the La Urbina neighborhood of the Sucre municipality, residents began to protest following the murder of a woman during a robbery, with the citizens demanding better police security while stating that four robberies occurred daily in the area.<ref>{{cite news|title=Video: Protestan en La Urbina por asesinato de señora|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2015/02/07/video-protestan-en-la-urbina-por-asesinato-de-senora/|accessdate=25 February 2015|agency=La Patilla|date=7 February 2015}}</ref> * '''9 February'''&nbsp;– Students in San Cristóbal protested demanding a response from [[PSUV]] leader and Táchira Governor [[José Gregorio Vielma Mora|Jose Vielma Mora]] who did not respond to a letter delivered to them.<ref name=FOXNEWS/><ref>{{cite news|last1=Evelyn Araiz|first1=Lorena|title=Estudiantes de dos universidades y un liceo protestaron en San Cristóbal|url=http://www.eluniversal.com/nacional-y-politica/150209/estudiantes-de-dos-universidades-y-un-liceo-protestaron-en-san-cristob|accessdate=25 February 2015|agency=[[El Universal (Caracas)|El Universal]]|date=9 February 2015}}</ref> * '''10 February'''&nbsp;– Three protesting students from the Catholic University of Táchira were injured from bullet wounds in San Cristóbal when the National Police fired at them while they were attempting to hide under vehicles from the police gunfire.<ref name=EUfeb10>{{cite news|last1=Evelyn Araiz|first1=Lorena|title=Tres estudiantes heridos de bala en la UCAT|url=http://www.eluniversal.com/nacional-y-politica/150210/tres-estudiantes-heridos-de-bala-en-la-ucat|accessdate=25 February 2015|agency=[[El Universal (Caracas)|El Universal]]|date=10 February 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Hieren de bala a tres estudiantes en protesta en la Universidad Católica del Táchira|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2015/02/10/hieren-de-bala-a-tres-estudiantes-en-protesta-en-la-universidad-catolica-del-tachira/|accessdate=25 February 2015|agency=La Patilla|date=10 February 2015}}</ref> Bullet holes were found on vehicles and shell casings were gathered, with the Catholic University of Táchira cancelled classes that day following the shooting.<ref name=EUfeb10/><ref>{{cite news|title=Táchira indignada; PNB hiere con balas a estudiantes de la Ucat (FOTOS)|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2015/02/10/tachira-indignada-pnb-hiere-con-balas-a-estudiantes-de-la-ucat-fotos/|accessdate=25 February 2015|agency=La Patilla|date=10 February 2015}}</ref> The Student Movement of Guyana announced a march for 12 February with the [[PSUV]] Student Movement responding to them by announcing a countermarch to confront the protesters at their march destination while also planning to support the National Guard.<ref>{{cite news|last1=de los Angeles Ramirez Cabello|first1=Maria|title=Estudiantes de Guayana marcharán el 12 F hasta lugar de protestas en 2014|url=http://www.eluniversal.com/nacional-y-politica/150210/estudiantes-de-guayana-marcharan-el-12-f-hasta-lugar-de-protestas-en-2|accessdate=25 February 2015|agency=El Universal|date=10 February 2015}}</ref> * '''11 February'''&nbsp;– Táchira governor José Gregorio Vielma Mora announced that Brigadier General Espinal Alexis Fernandez replaced Johnny Campos as National Police chief following the shooting that occurred the previous day of 3 Catholic University of Táchira students.<ref>{{cite news|title=Destituido jefe de la PNB en Táchira: Protestas se mantienen|url=http://el-carabobeno.com/portada/articulo/98607/destituido-jefe-de-la-pnb-en-tchira-protestas-se-mantienen|accessdate=25 February 2015|agency=[[El Carabobeño]]|date=11 February 2015}}</ref> * '''12 February'''&nbsp;– In Caracas and San Cristóbal hundreds marched to commemorate the beginning of protests in 2014.<ref name=REUT12F>{{cite news|last1=Cawthorne|first1=Andrew|last2=Farias|first2=Javier|title=Violence flares in Venezuela on anniversary of 2014 fatalities|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2015/02/12/us-venezuela-rallies-idUSKBN0LG2IC20150212|accessdate=25 February 2015|agency=[[Reuters]]|date=12 February 2015}}</ref> Clashes between police and protesters also occurred in both cities leading to injuries and arrests, with protesters throwing rocks and making barricades against police in Caracas and protesters throwing pipes and Molotov cocktails at police after they were confronted during a march in San Cristóbal.<ref name=REUT12F/> Government supporters also held a large demonstration numbered in the thousands in Caracas in support of President Maduro<ref name=REUT12F/> as well as a [[Youth Day]] concert in the city in celebration of the holiday. * '''13 February'''&nbsp;– According to Jose Vielma Mora, the governor of Tachira state and political ally of President Maduro stated that 11 people were arrested during street demonstrations on 12 February where fourteen National Police officers were injured in an attack.<ref name=FOXNEWS>{{cite news|title=14 Cops hurt in clashes in western Venezuela|url=http://latino.foxnews.com/latino/news/2015/02/13/14-cops-hurt-in-clashes-in-western-venezuela/|accessdate=17 February 2015|agency=Fox News Latina/EFE|date=13 February 2015}}</ref> A Tachira court had also ordered two police officers suspected of shooting at a student to be held pending formal charges of attempted homicide and unlawful use of their suspected of their service weapons.<ref name=FOXNEWS/> Protests occurred near Altamira Plaza on Francisco Miranda Avenue where protesters blocked traffic denouncing the arrests and commemorating the deaths of those killed in the 2014 protests.<ref>{{cite news|title=Protesta pacífica se alza en Altamira en memoria de los caídos #13F (Fotos)|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2015/02/13/protesta-pacifica-se-alza-en-altamira-en-memoria-de-los-caidos-13f-fotos/|accessdate=25 February 2015|agency=[[La Patilla]]|date=13 February 2015}}</ref> * '''14 February'''&nbsp;– Two protesters were released and one remained detained following the 12 February protests in San Cristóbal.<ref>{{cite news|title=Liberados con medidas cautelares estudiantes detenidos en Táchira el 12F|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2015/02/14/liberados-con-medidas-cautelares-estudiantes-detenidos-en-tachira-el-12f/|accessdate=25 February 2015|agency=[[La Patilla]]|date=14 February 2015}}</ref> * '''16 February'''&nbsp;– The Union of Workers of the Forest Enterprises announced a strike and protest, asking the government to complete promises made by former President Chavez involving upgrades in technology that was not completed that caused a drop in production while also demanding better pay.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Naim Malavé|first1=Jossie|title=Convocan huelga de "brazos caídos" para este miércoles en Maderas del Orinoco |url=http://nuevaprensa.com.ve/Convocan%20huelga%20de%20%E2%80%9Cbrazos%20ca%C3%ADdos%E2%80%9D%20para%20este%20mi%C3%A9rcoles%20en%20Maderas%20del%20Orinoco|accessdate=25 February 2015|agency=Nueva Prensa de Guyana|date=16 February 2015}}</ref> * '''19 February'''&nbsp;– Students near the Catholic University of Táchira protested against the government and some were injured by from rounds of buckshot fired at them.<ref>{{cite news|title=PNB cayó a perdigonazos a estudiantes de la Ucat (FOTOS)|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2015/02/19/pnb-cayo-a-perdigonazos-a-estudiantes-de-la-ucat-fotos/|accessdate=25 February 2015|agency=[[La Patilla]]|date=19 February 2015}}</ref> * '''20 February'''&nbsp;– In Caracas, demonstrations occurred denouncing the arrest of opposition mayor Antonio Ledezma on actions during the protests of the year before<ref>{{cite news|last1=Lee|first1=Brianna|title=Venezuela Arrest Sparks Fears Of Fresh Crackdown On Opposition|url=http://www.ibtimes.com/venezuela-arrest-sparks-fears-fresh-crackdown-opposition-1823524|accessdate=1 March 2015|agency=[[International Business Times]]|date=21 February 2015}}</ref> * '''22 February'''&nbsp;– Clashes occurred between students of the Catholic University of Táchira and Venezuelan authorities after the murders of two students who were bound and shot to death.<ref>{{cite news|title=Tres heridos en protestas en Táchira por asesinato de jóvenes estudiantes|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2015/02/22/tres-heridos-en-protestas-en-tachira-por-asesinato-de-jovenes-estudiantes/|accessdate=25 February 2015|agency=[[La Patilla]]|date=22 February 2015}}</ref> * '''24 February'''&nbsp;– The first death of the 2015 protests occurred during protests and clashes near the Catholic University of Táchira in San Cristóbal when Kluiberth Roa Nunez, a 14-year-old high school student, was fatally shot in the head by a National Police officer.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Schaefer Muñoz|first1=Sara|last2=Minaya|first2=Ezequiel|title=Shooting of Student Protester in Venezuela Ratchets Up Tension Police in riot gear were deployed to San Cristóbal, the epicenter of last year’s demonstrations|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/shooting-of-student-protester-in-venezuela-ratchets-up-tension-1424894647|accessdate=27 February 2015|agency=[[The Wall Street Journal]]|date=25 February 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Venezuelan 14-year-old shot dead during anti-government protest|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/feb/24/venezuelan-14-year-old-shot-dead-anti-government-protest|accessdate=27 February 2015|agency=[[The Guardian]]|date=24 February 2015}}</ref><ref name=LAHTroa>{{cite news|title=VenEconomy: Venezuela Breaks Down in Tears|url=http://www.laht.com/article.asp?ArticleId=2375812&CategoryId=10717|accessdate=27 February 2015|agency=[[Latin American Herald Tribune]]|date=24 February 2015}}</ref><ref name=EU1feb24>{{cite news|last1=Evelyn Arráiz|first1=Lorena|title=De un tiro en la cabeza asesinaron a estudiante en Táchira|url=http://www.eluniversal.com/nacional-y-politica/150224/de-un-tiro-en-la-cabeza-asesinaron-a-estudiante-en-tachira|accessdate=25 February 2015|agency=[[El Universal (Caracas)|El Universal]]|date=24 February 2015}}</ref> According to witnesses, Kluiberth, who had inadvertently come across the confrontation while leaving school, was hit while trying to take shelter under a car as protestors fled the police.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Castillo|first1=Mariano|title=Teen's death sparks new turmoil in Venezuela|url=http://www.cnn.com/2015/02/25/americas/venezuela-protest-teen-killed/|website=CNN|accessdate=27 February 2015}}</ref> One witness said the officer allegedly shot the 14-year-old at [[point blank]] range after he fell on the ground.<ref>{{cite news|title=Joven estudiante de Táchira habría sido asesinado ‘a quemarropa’ por uniformado del PNB, según dice testigo|url=http://ntn24ve.info/video/audio-venezuela-41355|accessdate=25 February 2015|agency=[[NTN24]]|date=24 February 2015}}</ref> The officer was arrested and President Maduro publicly condemned the killing.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Neuman|first1=William|title=Police Kill Boy During Protest in Venezuela|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/02/25/world/americas/police-kill-boy-during-protest-in-venezuela.html?_r=0|accessdate=25 February 2015|agency=[[The New York Times]]|date=24 February 2015}}</ref> According to Venezuelan government officials, 6 authorities were injured when protesters allegedly became violent, with officials stating they made barricades and used [[Molotov cocktail]]s.<ref name=EU1feb24/> * '''25 February'''&nbsp;– Students demonstrated with school books symbolically covered in fake blood near the headquarters of the Ministry of Interior, Justice and Peace in the Libertador municipality demanding Minister [[Carmen Melendez Teresa Rivas]] to investigate the death of Kluiberth Roa Nunez and to repeal Resolution 8610, a resolution that grants Venezuelan authorities to use deadly force against protesters.<ref>{{cite news|last1=de la Rosa|first1=Alicia|title=Estudiantes exigen justicia por muerte de liceísta y derogar Resolución|url=http://www.eluniversal.com/nacional-y-politica/150225/estudiantes-exigen-justicia-por-muerte-de-liceista-y-derogar-resolucio|accessdate=25 February 2015|agency=[[El Universal (Caracas)|El Universal]]|date=25 February 2015}}</ref> In [[Barinas, Venezuela|Barinas]], students of Universidad Santa María protested against the use of deadly force against protesters while also denouncing the killing of Roa Nunez and demanded the repeal of Resolution 8610.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Obregon|first1=Walter|title=Estudiantes de Barinas protestaron en contra del asesinato de liceísta|url=http://www.eluniversal.com/nacional-y-politica/150225/estudiantes-de-barinas-protestaron-en-contra-del-asesinato-de-liceista|accessdate=25 February 2015|agency=[[El Universal (Caracas)|El Universal]]|date=25 February 2015}}</ref> * '''26 February'''&nbsp;– Residents in Mérida protested against the killing of Kluiberth Roa Nunez and sang the National Anthem.<ref>{{cite news|title=Merideños protestan pacíficamente en El Campito (FOTOS)|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2015/02/26/meridenos-protestan-pacificamente-en-el-campito-fotos/|accessdate=1 March 2015|agency=[[La Patilla]]|date=26 February 2015}}</ref> * '''27 February'''&nbsp;– Students began to collect signatures to repeal Resolution 8610, a regulation that allows the use of deadly force to control protests.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Dreier|first1=Hannah|title=Venezuelan Protest Deadly Force Order After Young Boy Killed|url=http://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/venezuelan-students-protest-deadly-force-order-29273459|accessdate=1 March 2015|agency=[[ABC News]]|date=27 February 2015}}</ref> * '''28 February'''&nbsp;– Thousands marched in San Cristóbal denouncing the crackdown by President Maduro and the killing of Kluiberth Roa Nunez, with María Corina Machado and Kluiberth's parents participating in the march.<ref>{{cite news|title=La marcha por la Paz desborda San Cristóbal (Fotos)|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2015/02/28/la-marcha-por-la-paz-desborda-san-cristobal-fotos/|accessdate=1 March 2015|agency=[[La Patilla]]|date=28 February 2015}}</ref> Opposition groups began gathering signatures for the National Agreement for the Transition in various cities throughout Venezuela.<ref>{{cite news|title=Voluntad Popular recolectó firmas por el cambio pacífico y constitucional (Fotos)|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2015/03/01/voluntad-popular-recolecto-firmas-por-el-cambio-pacifico-y-constitucional-fotos/|accessdate=7 March 2015|agency=[[La Patilla]]|date=1 March 2015}}</ref>
==March== * '''2 March'''&nbsp;– In Mérida, armed groups of [[Colectivo (Venezuela)|colectivos]] reportedly attacked the University of Los Andes, supposedly to intimidate the protest site, shooting guns at students and faculty while also holding 3 students hostage and stealing belongings of students.<ref>{{cite news|title=Estudiantes de la ULA denunciaron ataques de colectivos|url=http://www.eluniversal.com/nacional-y-politica/150302/estudiantes-de-la-ula-denunciaron-ataques-de-colectivos|accessdate=3 March 2015|agency=[[El Universal (Caracas)|El Universal]]|date=2 March 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=León|first1=Leonardo|title=Colectivos motorizados armados entraron a núcleo de ULA-Mérida y dispararon|url=http://www.el-nacional.com/sucesos/Colectivos-motorizados-entraron-ULA-Merida-dispararon_0_584341702.html|accessdate=3 March 2015|agency=[[El Nacional (Caracas)|El Nacional]]|date=2 March 2015}}</ref> In Valera, Trujillo state, students protested over the death of Kluiberth Roa Nunez which led to clashes between the protesters and Venezuelan authorities.<ref>{{cite news|title=GNB y Policía Municipal de Trujillo reprimen protesta de liceístas en Valera este #2M|url=http://www.venezuelaaldia.com/2015/03/gnb-y-policia-municipal-de-trujillo-reprimen-protesta-de-liceistas-en-valera-este-2m/|accessdate=3 March 2015|agency=Venezuela Al Día|date=2 March 2015}}</ref> * '''4 March'''&nbsp;– Protests began in at least six communities between Bolivar state and Delta Amacuro with the communities and their councils complaining about problems with utilities in the area.<ref name=NPGmarch5>{{cite news|last1=Galvis M.|first1=Vanessa|title=Siguen protestas en Río Claro por falta de agua potable|url=http://www.nuevaprensa.com.ve/Siguen%20protestas%20en%20R%C3%ADo%20Claro%20por%20falta%20de%20agua%20potable|accessdate=7 March 2015|agency=Nueva Prensa de Guyana|date=5 March 2015}}</ref> * '''5 March'''&nbsp;– Protests over inadequate utilities in the multiple communities between Bolivar state and Delta Amacuro continued for a second day.<ref name=NPGmarch5/> * '''6 March'''&nbsp;– Francisco Miranda Avenue near Parque del Este and Parque Cristal in Caracas were blocked by protesters in the evening hours.<ref>{{cite news|title=Manifestantes cierran avenida Francisco Miranda #6M (Fotos)|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2015/03/06/manifestantes-cierran-avenida-francisco-miranda-6m-fotos/|accessdate=14 March 2015|agency=La Patilla|date=6 March 2015}}</ref> * '''8 March'''&nbsp;– While commemorating [[International Women's Day]] in Caracas, mothers along with their husbands and children participated in a march led by María Corina Machado, condemning Resolution 8610.<ref>{{cite news|title=Madres venezolanas tomaron las calles en defensa de sus hijos (Video)|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2015/03/08/madres-venezolanas-tomaron-las-calles-en-defensa-de-sus-hijos-video/|accessdate=14 March 2015|agency=La Patilla|date=8 March 2015}}</ref> Women in Mérida marched denouncing Resolution 8610 and demanded justice for students and young individuals who were killed during the protests.<ref>{{cite news|title=Mujeres merideñas marcharon para exigir justicia con los jóvenes asesinados|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2015/03/08/mujeres-meridenas-marcharon-para-exigir-justicia-con-los-jovenes-asesinados/|accessdate=14 March 2015|agency=La Patilla|date=8 March 2015}}</ref> * '''10 March'''&nbsp;– Students of medicine at the Central University of Venezuela protested against the health crisis in Venezuela and demanded solutions.<ref name=LPmarzo10>{{cite news|title=Estudiantes y médicos protestaron en la UCV para exigir solución a la crisis (Fotos)|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2015/03/10/estudiantes-y-medicos-protestan-en-la-ucv-para-exigir-solucion-a-la-crisis-fotos/|accessdate=14 March 2015|agency=La Patilla|date=10 March 2015}}</ref> In Tachira and Valencia, residents also protested against the health crisis demanded improvements in health care centers.<ref name=LPmarzo10/> * '''11 March'''&nbsp;– Students at the Central University of Venezuela protested against insecurity in the area.<ref>{{cite news|title=En fotos: Ucevistas alzaron la voz contra la delincuencia|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2015/03/11/en-fotos-ucevistas-alzaron-la-voz-contra-la-delincuencia/|accessdate=14 March 2015|agency=La Patilla|date=11 March 2015}}</ref> * '''12 March'''&nbsp;–Rodolfo Gonzalez, a retired commercial pilot arrested for allegedly operating violent protests, commits suicide in the headquarters of [[SEBIN]].<ref name=ECpilot>{{cite news|last1=Hernández|first1=Alicia|title=Más allá de las caras conocidas: los presos políticos en Venezuela Leer más: Beyond the familiar faces: political prisoners in Venezuela. World News http://bit.ly/1xp8KDT|url=http://www.elconfidencial.com/mundo/2015-03-20/mas-alla-de-las-caras-conocidas-los-presos-politicos-en-venezuela_731327/|accessdate=22 March 2015|agency=El Confidencial|date=20 March 2015}}</ref> * '''16 March'''&nbsp;– Outside of the National Experimental University of Táchira, an unidentified group of protesters blocked roads and burned a vehicle.<ref>{{cite news|title=Camión es quemado durante protesta en los alrededores de la UNET (+Fotos)|url=http://www.venezuelaaldia.com/2015/03/camion-es-quemado-durante-protesta-en-los-alrededores-de-la-unet-fotos/|accessdate=22 March 2015|agency=Venezuela Al Día|date=16 March 2015}}</ref> * '''17 March'''&nbsp;– Teachers across Venezuela planned a nationwide strike after Minister of Education, Hector Rodriguez, denied to fix wages that had become inadequate due to the high level of inflation in Venezuela.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Mendéz|first1=Gustavo|title=Docentes convocan "paro activo" para exigir aumento|url=http://www.eluniversal.com/nacional-y-politica/150317/docentes-convocan-paro-activo-para-exigir-aumento|accessdate=22 March 2015|agency=[[El Universal (Caracas)|El Universal]]|date=17 March 2015}}</ref> Protester Christian Holdack, who was processed alongside [[Leopoldo López]], was released from prison.<ref name=UNImarch18>{{cite news|title=Venezuela liberó a tres opositores detenidos durante protestas el año pasado|url=http://noticias.univision.com/article/2276464/2015-03-18/america-latina/venezuela/venezuela-libero-a-tres-opositores-detenidos-durate-protestas-el-ano-pasado|accessdate=22 March 2015|agency=[[Univision]]|date=18 March 2015}}</ref> * '''18 March'''&nbsp;– Three protesters detained since 2014, Julver Pulido, Juan Esqueda and Miguel Ángel Nieto, are released from prison and granted probation.<ref name=UNImarch18/> * '''20 March'''&nbsp;– Three students were arrested while protesting in Altamira Square and were held at the SEBIN headquarters.<ref>{{cite news|title=Confirman detención en El Helicoide de cuatro estudiantes que estaban en Altamira|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2015/03/21/confirman-detencion-arbitraria-en-el-helicoide-de-cuatro-estudiantes-que-estaban-en-plaza-francia/|accessdate=23 March 2015|agency=La Patilla|date=21 March 2015}}</ref> * '''21 March'''&nbsp;– Another protest was allegedly arrested by SEBIN plainclothes officers while protesting in Altamira Square.<ref>{{cite news|title=Presuntos funcionarios detienen a otro joven en Altamira mientras protestaba (Fotos)|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2015/03/21/presuntos-funcionarios-detienen-a-otro-joven-en-altamira-mientras-protestaba-fotos/|accessdate=23 March 2015|agency=La Patilla|date=21 March 2015}}</ref> Residents in San José and Rio Chico, Miranda state protested against insecurity and blocked roads following a murder occurring in the area.<ref>{{cite news|title=VENEZUELA: Cerrada vía a Río Chico en protesta por asesinato de transportista|url=http://www.entornointeligente.com/articulo/5394310/VENEZUELA-Cerrada-via-a-Rio-Chico-en-protesta-por-asesinato-de-transportista-21032015|accessdate=22 March 2015|agency=Etorno Inteligente|date=21 March 2015}}</ref> * '''24 March'''&nbsp;– After attempted kidnappings and murders of children in neighborhoods of Caracas allegedly for [[organ harvesting]], residents in Petare of the Sucre Municipality and near Altamira protested.<ref name=COPE>{{cite news|title=Maduro acusa a Felipe González de apoyar un golpe "contra Venezuela"|url=http://www.cope.es/detalle/Maduro-acusa-a-Felipe-Gonzalez-de-apoyar-un-golpe-contra-Venezuela.html?id=2015032512540001|accessdate=26 March 2015|agency=[[Cadena COPE]]|date=25 March 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Motorizados y vecinos manifestaron contra inseguridad en Petare y Altamira|url=http://www.eluniversal.com/sucesos/150324/motorizados-y-vecinos-manifestaron-contra-inseguridad-en-petare-y-alta|accessdate=26 March 2015|agency=[[El Universal (Caracas)|El Universal]]|date=24 March 2015}}</ref> Hundreds of motorcyclists protested by blocking streets throughout Caracas and shortly gathered to protest in front of the [[Venezolana de Television]] (VTV) headquarters.<ref>{{cite news|title=Motorizados cerraron Petare en protesta al presunto robo de niños en el país (+Tuits)|url=http://www.venezuelaaldia.com/2015/03/motorizados-cerraron-petare-en-protesta-al-presunto-robo-de-ninos-en-el-pais-tuits/|accessdate=26 March 2015|agency=Venezuela Al Día|date=24 March 2015}}</ref> President Maduro called the allegations false and blamed the opposition of the allegations.<ref name=COPE/> Mayor of [[Sucre, Miranda|Sucre]], [[Carlos Ocariz]], stated that formal complaints were made concerning the kidnapping of children.<ref name=COPE/> * '''25 March'''&nbsp;– Drivers near Petare protested against insecurity by blocking access to the area with trucks and buses.<ref>{{cite news|title=Transportistas trancan la autopista GMA|url=http://www.el-nacional.com/caracas/Transportistas-trancan-autopista-GMA_0_598140297.html|accessdate=26 March 2015|agency=[[El Nacional (Caracas)|El Nacional)]]|date=25 March 2015}}</ref>
==April== * '''5 April'''&nbsp;– In acts of protest against the Venezuelan government and the United States government, both pro-government and opposition individuals burned effigies of various officials during some traditional [[Easter]] celebrations of the [[Burning of Judas]].<ref name=LPjudas>{{cite news|title=Muñecos de Obama y Maduro arden en la Quema de Judas (Fotos)|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2015/04/05/munecos-de-obama-y-maduro-arden-en-la-quema-de-judas-en-caracas/|accessdate=7 April 2015|agency=La Patilla|date=6 April 2015}}</ref> Government supporters burned dolls representing United States president Barack Obama and opposition official Henrique Capriles with the preparation of one burning of a President Obama effigy shared on Venezuelan state television.<ref name=LPjudas/><ref>{{cite news|title=Chavistas queman a "Judas Obama" con cara de Izarra ¿WTF?|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2015/04/05/chavistas-queman-a-judas-obama-con-cara-de-izarra-wtf/|accessdate=7 April 2015|agency=La Patilla|date=5 April 2015}}</ref> Meanwhile, individuals supporting the opposition burned effigies of President Maduro, Diosdado Cabello and other Venezuelan officials.<ref name=LPjudas/> * '''6 April'''&nbsp;– Workers of the University Clinical Hospital announced that they may protest again so that their calls for more resources will be heard since dialogue with the Ministry of Health had slowed.<ref>{{cite news|title=Obreros del Hospital Clínico Universitario retomarán protestas|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2015/04/06/obreros-del-hospital-clinico-universitario-retomaran-protestas/|accessdate=7 April 2015|agency=La Patilla|date=6 April 2015}}</ref> In the community of Los Ejidos, residents blocked a road in protest over the lack of water for over six months in the area leaving over 1,550 without water while others protested over the alleged raise of fares for transportation in the area.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Vidal|first1=Brian|title=Cerrada vía a Humocaro como protesta por falta de agua y transporte|url=http://elimpulso.com/articulo/cerrada-via-a-el-tocuyo-como-protesta-por-falta-de-agua-y-transporte#|accessdate=7 April 2015|agency=''[[El Impulso (Venezuela)|El Impulso]]''|date=6 April 2015}}</ref> * '''13 April'''&nbsp;– Outside of the Ministry of Popular Power for Health, Ministry of Popular Power for Health workers protested for better working and patient conditions and demanded to receive pay they had not received.<ref>{{cite news|title=Trabajadores del Clínico Universitario protestaron frente a MinSalud|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2015/04/13/trabajadores-del-clinico-universitario-protestaron-frente-a-minsalud/|accessdate=28 April 2015|agency=[[La Patilla]]|date=13 April 2015}}</ref> * '''14 April'''&nbsp;– In Puerto la Cruz, protesters blocked streets by burning tires in the road near a state-run [[PDVAL]] store.<ref>{{cite news|title=Trancada Vía Alterna de Puerto La Cruz por protesta|url=http://www.el-nacional.com/regiones/Trancada-Via-Alterna-Puerto-Cruz_0_610138982.html|accessdate=28 April 2015|agency=''[[El Nacional (Caracas)|El Nacional]]''|date=14 April 2015}}</ref> * '''15 April'''&nbsp;– At the Central University of Venezuela, workers protested over disagreements of collective agreements and were cordoned from moving by the National Guard.<ref>{{cite news|title=Protesta cierra accesos hacia la UCV por Plaza Venezuela|url=http://www.2001.com.ve/con-la-gente/94713/protesta-cierra-accesos-hacia-la-ucv-por-plaza-venezuela-.html|accessdate=28 April 2015|agency=''[[Diario 2001]]''|date=15 April 2015}}</ref> * '''24 April'''&nbsp;– Protesters demonstrated outside of a state-run PDVAL market again in Puerto la Cruz after citizens reported that they were withholding appliances from being sold to customers with three men stating that they were attacked by police.<ref>{{cite news|title=Protestaron frente a Pdval por venta de equipos|url=http://eltiempo.com.ve/locales/puertocruz/protesta/protestaron-frente-a-pdval-por-venta-de-equipos/179347|accessdate=28 April 2015|agency=''[[El Tiempo (Anzoátegui)|El Tiempo]]''|date=24 April 2015}}</ref> * '''25 April'''&nbsp;– In Caracas, protests occurred on Cafe Avenue, specifically near San Luis Boulevard with individuals denouncing increasing crime in the city.<ref>{{cite news|title=Reportan protesta en el Cafetal|url=http://www.el-nacional.com/politica/Reportan-protesta-Cafetal_0_616738399.html|accessdate=28 April 2015|agency=''[[El Nacional (Caracas)|El Nacional]]''|date=25 April 2015}}</ref>
==May== * '''1 May'''&nbsp;– Protesters Pablo Estrada, Eduardo Colmenares, Raul López and Rosa Rivas, all arrested in July 2014, were released according to their lawyers.<ref>{{cite news|title=Abogados confirman liberación de cuatro detenidos por protestar|url=http://eltiempo.com.ve/venezuela/medida/abogados-confirman-liberacion-de-cuatro-detenidos-por-protestar/180233|accessdate=20 May 2015|agency=''[[El Tiempo (Anzoátegui)|El Tiempo]]''|date=1 May 2015}}</ref> * '''2 May'''&nbsp;– Resident of [[23 de Enero]] protested due to the lack of gas in the area which lasted several days.<ref>{{cite news|title=En 23 de Enero protestan por falta de gas|url=http://www.2001.com.ve/con-la-gente/96163/en-23-de-enero-protestan-por-falta-de-gas-.html|accessdate=20 May 2015|agency=''[[Diario 2001]]''|date=2 May 2015}}</ref> * '''7 May'''&nbsp;– Central University of Venezuela students protested against insecurity by blocking access to Plaza Venezuela following the murder of a student on the previous day.<ref>{{cite news |title=Estudiantes cierran accesos de la UCV en protesta por la inseguridad |url=http://www.eluniversal.com/sucesos/150507/estudiantes-cierran-accesos-de-la-ucv-en-protesta-por-la-inseguridad |accessdate=20 May 2015 |agency=''[[El Universal (Caracas)|El Universal]]'' |date=7 May 2015}}</ref> * '''11 May'''&nbsp;– Residents of the town of Clarines blocked roads and burned tires in the roads while protesting the lack of water in their homes for over a month, with Mayor Maico Marrero going to the protest and began distributing water with tanker trucks.<ref>{{cite news|title=Residentes de Clarines cerraron la troncal 9 por falta de agua|url=http://eltiempo.com.ve/locales/regionales/protesta/residentes-de-clarines-cerraron-la-troncal-9-por-falta-de-agua/181383|accessdate=20 May 2015|agency=''[[El Tiempo (Anzoátegui)|El Tiempo]]''|date=11 May 2015}}</ref> Citizens of Carabobo protested blocking roads demanding the allocation of homes to them.<ref>{{cite news|title=VENEZUELA: Parcialmente cerrada Autopista Sur por protesta vecinal|url=http://www.entornointeligente.com/articulo/5893154/VENEZUELA-Parcialmente-cerrada-Autopista-Sur-por-protesta-vecinal|accessdate=20 May 2015|agency=Entorno Inteligente|date=11 May 2015}}</ref> * '''15 May'''&nbsp;– Student leader Conan Quintana was robbed and murdered along with another person two blocks away from the Ministry of Interior and Justice headquarters, resulting in immediate protests near the headquarters following the murder.<ref>{{cite news|title=Protestan frente al MIJ por asesinato del dirigente estudiantil Conan Quintana (+Tuits)|url=http://www.venezuelaaldia.com/2015/05/otra-muerte-injusta-protestan-frente-al-mij-por-asesinato-del-dirigente-estudiantil-conan-quintana-tuits/|accessdate=20 May 2015|agency=Venezuela Al Dia|date=15 May 2015}}</ref> * '''16 May'''&nbsp;– Over 150 people protested in Caracas outside of the headquarters of the Ministry of Interior and Justice following the murder of Conan Quintana.<ref name=ET16m>{{cite news|title=Jóvenes protestaron por asesinato de dirigente estudiantil|url=http://eltiempo.com.ve/venezuela/protesta/jovenes-protestaron-por-asesinato-de-dirigente-estudiantil/181898|accessdate=20 May 2015|agency=''[[El Tiempo (Anzoátegui)|El Tiempo]]''|date=16 May 2015}}</ref> In Mérida, students also protested against the murder of Quintana blocking Las Américas Avenue, resulting with Polimérida officers firing buckshot at demonstrators in order to disperse them.<ref name=ET16m/> * '''18 May'''&nbsp;– In [[San Bernardino, Libertador, Caracas|San Bernardino]], mothers of cancer patients protested outside of Jose Manuel de los Rios Children's Hospital due to the lack of care for their children who had not received treatment for at least five months.<ref>{{cite news|title=Madres desesperadas protestan por falta de quimioterapias para sus niños|url=http://www.entornointeligente.com/articulo/5960764/VENEZUELA-LA-PROTESTA-MAS-DOLOROSA-Madres-desesperadas-protestan-por-falta-de-quimioterapias-para-sus-ninos-18052015|accessdate=20 May 2015|agency=Entorno Inteligente|date=18 May 2015}}</ref> * '''19 May'''&nbsp;– Hundreds of people protested in Táchira for various causes ranging from payments to utility issues.<ref>{{cite news|title=VENEZUELA: Jornada de protestas se registraron este martes en Táchira|url=http://www.entornointeligente.com/articulo/5970507/VENEZUELA-Jornada-de-protestas-se-registraron-este-martes-en-Tachira-19052015|accessdate=20 May 2015|agency=Entorno Inteligente|date=19 May 2015}}</ref> * '''23 May'''&nbsp;– Following a report that opposition leader Daniel Ceballos was being moved to one of Venezuela's most violent public prisons, Cabellos and Leopoldo López announced that they were beginning a [[hunger strike]] and called on Venezuelans to conduct a mass-protest the next week.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Rueda|first1=Jorge|title=Jailed Venezuelan leader starts hunger strike, urges protest|url=http://bigstory.ap.org/article/d78e2c9cb84b4c868bed09f8e3aa56bd/venezuela-transfers-prominent-opponent-violent-prison|accessdate=24 May 2015|agency=[[Associated Press]]|date=23 May 2015}}</ref> * '''26 May'''&nbsp;– About 500 educational workers protested outside of Miraflores Palace and demanded that a representative of President Maduro hear about their complications with pay and benefits.<ref>{{cite news|title=Docentes protestan a la entrada del Palacio de Miraflores|url=http://www.eluniversal.com/caracas/150526/docentes-protestan-a-la-entrada-del-palacio-de-miraflores|accessdate=27 May 2015|agency=''[[El Universal (Caracas)|El Universal]]''|date=26 May 2015}}</ref> * '''27 May'''&nbsp;– The opposition coalition announced that they would not participate in the 30 May demonstrations, though opposition leader Henrique Capriles stated he would personally participate.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Dreier|first1=Hannah|title=Planned March Shows Cracks in Venezuela Opposition Movement|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Business/photos/photos-celebrity-homes-6636854/image-indie-director-cameo-actor-mark-duplass-buys-home-31313293|accessdate=29 May 2015|agency=[[ABC News]]|date=27 May 2015}}</ref> * '''28 May'''&nbsp;– Hundreds of students in Zulia marched demanding respect to human rights and more security.<ref>{{cite news|title=Movimiento estudiantil zuliano tomó las calles para exigir seguridad y respeto de los DDHH|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2015/05/28/movimiento-estudiantil-zuliano-tomo-las-calles-para-exigir-seguridad-y-respeto-de-los-ddhh/|accessdate=29 May 2015|agency=[[La Patilla]]|date=28 May 2015}}</ref> Taxi drivers in Petare in Caracas protested against insecurity blocking roads in the neighborhood.<ref>{{cite news|title=Taxistas protestan en Palo Verde por la inseguridad (Fotos)|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2015/05/28/taxistas-protestan-en-palo-verde-por-la-inseguridad-fotos/|accessdate=29 May 2015|agency=[[La Patilla]]|date=28 May 2015}}</ref> * '''30 May'''&nbsp;– About 200,000 Venezuelans protested throughout the country by marching in cities like Maracaibo, Valencia, Barquisimeto and Caracas to demand the release of those arrested during the preceding protests and to pressure the Venezuelan government into setting a date for the congressional elections, fearing that government will cancel the vote to maintain power.<ref name=WSJmay30>{{cite news|last1=Minaya|first1=Ezequiel|title=Venezuela’s Opposition Supporters Protest Government Thousands march to back a jailed opposition leader, who has gone on a hunger strike|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/venezuelas-opposition-supporters-protest-government-1433019209|accessdate=31 May 2015|agency=''[[The Wall Street Journal]]''|date=30 May 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Tayler|first1=Jeffrey|title=Venezuela’s Last Hope|url=https://foreignpolicy.com/2015/06/10/venezuelas-last-hope-leopoldo-lopez-maduro/|accessdate=11 June 2015|agency=''[[Foreign Policy]]''|date=10 June 2015}}</ref>
==June== * '''8 June'''&nbsp;– A group of students from the Federation of University Centers of the University of Zulia began a hunger strike to bring international attention to the crisis in Venezuela.<ref>{{cite news|title=Movimiento estudiantil zuliano inició huelga de hambre por violación de derechos democráticos del país|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2015/06/08/movimiento-estudiantil-zuliano-inicio-huelga-de-hambre-por-violacion-de-derechos-democraticos-del-pais/|accessdate=30 June 2015|agency=[[La Patilla]]|date=8 June 2015}}</ref> * '''11 June'''&nbsp;– The National Guard arrested seven opposition leaders who wanted to start a hunger strike in front of the National Electoral Council (CNE) headquarters in Caracas.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Alejandro Urdaneta|first1=José|title=Detienen a opositores que iban a iniciar una huelga de hambre|url=http://www.laverdad.com/politica/76809-detienen-a-opositores-que-iban-a-iniciar-una-huelga-de-hambre.html|accessdate=30 June 2015|agency=[[La Verdad (Maracaibo)|La Verdad]]|date=11 June 2015}}</ref> * '''14 June'''&nbsp;– Hunger strikers at the Maria Auxiliadora in Trujillo were allegedly attacked by Venezuelan authorities.<ref>{{cite news|title=De madrugada y con arma en mano, atacaron a jóvenes huelguistas en Valera (+ tuits)|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2015/06/14/de-madrugada-y-con-arma-en-mano-atacaron-a-jovenes-huelguistas-en-valera-tuits/|accessdate=30 June 2015|agency=[[La Patilla]]|date=14 June 2015}}</ref> * '''18 June'''&nbsp;– Brazilian senators, including Ronaldo Caiado and [[Aécio Neves]], denounce that they were unable to visit Leopoldo López due to having their access blocked and being attacked by government supporters.<ref>http://www.eluniversal.com/nacional-y-politica/150618/senadores-brasilenos-denuncian-ataque-y-bloqueo-a-su-comitiva-en-carac</ref><ref>http://www.elsoldemargarita.com.ve/posts/post/id:152000/Atacaron-veh%C3%ADculo-de-delegaci%C3%B3n-de-senadores-brasile%C3%B1os-en-Venezuela</ref><ref>http://elperiodicovenezolano.com/atentado-oficialistas-atacan-autobus-de-senadores-brasilenos-fotos/</ref> Farmers in Araure held a march demanding the Venezuelan government to make actions combatting shortages and criticized the frequent changing of ministers.<ref>{{cite news|title=Agropecuarios protestaron en gran marcha por indolencia gubernamental hacia el sector (FOTOS)|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2015/06/18/productores-agropecuarios-protestaron-en-gran-marcha-por-indolencia-gubernamental-hacia-el-sector-fotos/|accessdate=30 June 2015|agency=[[La Patilla]]|date=18 June 2015}}</ref> * '''19 June'''&nbsp;– Empresas Polar workers protested against the Venezuelan government, denouncing the lack of raw materials and the refusal to distribute needed currency to the company.<ref>{{cite news|title=Trabajadores de Empresas Polar protestan por falta de materia prima y divisas (Fotos y video)|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2015/06/19/trabajadores-de-empresas-polar-protestan-por-falta-de-materia-prima-y-divisas-fotos-y-video/|accessdate=30 June 2015|agency=[[La Patilla]]|date=19 June 2015}}</ref> * '''22 June'''&nbsp;– A caravan of public transportation drivers protested on Prados del Este highway due to the shortages of parts and tires, stating they would deliver a letter to the Interior Minister at Plaza Venezuela.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Cañizález|first1=Migdalis|title=Caravana de transportistas fue detenida en plaza Venezuela|url=http://www.eluniversal.com/caracas/150622/caravana-de-transportistas-fue-detenida-en-plaza-venezuela|accessdate=30 June 2015|agency=[[El Universal (Caracas)|El Universal]]|date=22 June 2015}}</ref> * '''23 June'''&nbsp;– Leopoldo Lopez ended his hunger strike after one of his demands, the announcement of parliamentary elections, was fulfilled when the National Electoral Council declared the holding of elections on 6 December for MPs of the National Assembly.<ref>{{cite news|title=Venezuela opposition leader Leopoldo Lopez ends hunger strike|url=http://www.euronews.com/2015/06/24/venezuela-opposition-leader-leopoldo-lopez-ends-hunger-strike/|accessdate=30 June 2015|agency=[[Euronews]]|date=24 June 2015}}</ref> Other organizations ended their nearly month-long hunger strikes along with Lopez.<ref>{{cite news|title=Jóvenes en la Iglesia Guadalupe levantan huelga de hambre|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2015/06/23/jovenes-levantan-huelga-de-hambre-en-la-iglesia-de-guadalupe/|accessdate=30 June 2015|agency=[[La Patilla]]|date=23 June 2015}}</ref> * '''25 June'''&nbsp;– On Margarita Island, residents who had to wait in lines at markets like the government-run PDVAL and Makro began to protest blocking roads.<ref>{{cite news|title=Hacían cola en Makro de Margarita, pero decidieron trancar la vía como protesta|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2015/06/25/hacian-cola-en-makro-de-margarita-pero-decidieron-trancar-la-via-como-protesta/|accessdate=30 June 2015|agency=[[La Patilla]]|date=25 June 2015}}</ref> * '''26 June'''&nbsp;– A march was held from the headquarters of Ciudad Banesco in Monte Bello to Chacaito Brion Square that was organized by the National Journalists Council (CNP) and the Federation of University Teachers of Venezuela (FAPUV).<ref name=LPjune26>{{cite news|title=Así está la marcha por la libertad de expresión y autonomía universitaria (Fotos)|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2015/06/26/asi-esta-la-marcha-por-la-libertad-de-expresion-y-autonomia-universitaria-fotos/|accessdate=30 June 2015|agency=[[La Patilla]]|date=26 June 2015}}</ref> The groups of journalists demonstrated for freedom of expression and to denounce attacks on journalists.<ref name=LPjune26/> * '''29 June'''&nbsp;– Motorcycle taxi drivers protested in front of the headquarters of the governor of Lara state, denouncing alleged harassment from Venezuelan authorities.<ref>{{cite news|title=#29J Mototaxistas queman cauchos frente a la Gobernación de Lara (Foto + Audio)|url=http://elimpulso.com/articulo/29j-mototaxistas-queman-cauchos-frente-a-la-gobernacion-de-lara-foto-audio#|accessdate=30 June 2015|agency=[[El Impulso (Venezuela)|El Impulso]]|date=29 June 2015}}</ref>
==July== * '''16 July'''&nbsp;– Ministry of Environment and Housing workers protested demanding President Maduro to increase their salaries.<ref>{{cite news|title=Protesta de trabajadores del Ministerio de Vivienda restringe el paso en Chacao (Fotos)|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2015/07/16/protesta-de-trabajadores-del-ministerio-de-vivienda-restringe-el-paso-en-chacao-fotos/|accessdate=23 July 2015|agency=[[La Patilla]]|date=16 July 2015}}</ref> * '''17 July'''&nbsp;– In Barinas residents protested, blocking a route to Mérida due to the lack of food and basic necessities demanding Mayor Luis Henriquez of the Bolivar municipality to perform the necessary acts to acquire such goods.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Obregón|first1=Walter|title=Protesta de vecinos impide paso de Barinas a Mérida|url=http://www.eluniversal.com/nacional-y-politica/150717/protesta-de-vecinos-impide-paso-de-barinas-a-merida|accessdate=23 July 2015|agency=''[[El Universal (Caracas)|El Universal]]''|date=17 July 2015}}</ref> * '''20 July'''&nbsp;– In Catia, residents protested against insecurity and demanded that Venezuelan authorities initiate patrols in the area to combat crime.<ref>{{cite news|title=En video: Comunidad de Alta Vista protesta por inseguridad|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2015/07/20/en-video-comunidad-de-alta-vista-protesta-por-inseguridad/|accessdate=23 July 2015|agency=[[La Patilla]]|date=20 July 2015}}</ref>
==August== * '''8 August'''&nbsp;– A demonstration against shortages in Venezuela was held in eastern Caracas following the death of man during looting.<ref name=FNLaugust9>{{cite news|title=Venezuelan opposition take to the streets in protest against crime, hunger|url=http://latino.foxnews.com/latino/news/2015/08/09/venezuelan-opposition-take-to-streets-in-protest-against-crime-hunger/|accessdate=15 August 2015|agency=[[Fox News Latino]]|date=9 August 2015}}</ref> The protest involved hundreds of people, though the number of those participating was smaller than previous demonstrations possibly due to Venezuelans being preoccupied with finding food and other products.<ref name=FNLaugust9/>
